<p>I have a pretty simple script to force downloads from S3.</p>  <pre><code>$headers = $this-&gt;s3-&gt;getObjectHeaders(array('Bucket' =&gt; $bucket, 'Key' =&gt; $s3name));     $headerArray = $headers-&gt;toArray();      // force download in this case     header("Content-disposition: attachment; filename=\"{$filename}\"");      if (ob_get_level()) {       ob_end_flush();     }      flush();      readfile("s3://{$bucket}/{$s3name}");      exit;     return; </code></pre>  <p>If I remove the "exit", the resulting downloaded file contains extra content at the end.  </p>  <p>In the case of a JSON file, it adds {}.  </p>  <p>If there was a bug AFTER readfile, the HTML error content of the bug is APPENDED to the downloaded file.</p>  <p>I can STOP this unwanted action by simply adding exit.  BUT, this prevents me from doing any more processing at that point.</p>  <p>I've tried ob_end_flush(), etc, but to no avail.</p>  <p>Any ideas?</p>